{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure risk is module handoff (history manager -> prompt builder -> LLM client), not pure slicing logic. Integration is the lowest level that verifies the trimmed set is what is actually sent downstream. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior text only requires 'trimmed to the most recent 10 messages' and does not require judging model output quality or multi-agentic decision quality.","test_description":"Run the real in-process chat pipeline with a 15+ message history and a stub LLM transport; assert the outbound LLM request contains exactly the last 10 messages in correct order and roles.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output quality (relevance/on-topicness). Stubs or mocks would hide this failure by returning pre-approved answers. Rejected Workflow because behavior describes a single generation quality check, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Execute prompts against the real target model with representative customer questions and evaluate topical relevance (rubric or LLM-as-judge with calibrated threshold) across repeated runs to account for variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"The phrase 'correctly identifies' makes correctness depend on real model judgment of tone; deterministic fakes can validate trigger wiring but not tone-classification quality. Rejected Workflow because the core claim is one agentic decision (too-formal detection) governing handoff; regeneration triggering can be asserted deterministically once detection occurs.","test_description":"Feed real overly formal candidate responses for casual-tier cases through the production tone-check path (real model call), assert they are flagged as too formal at acceptable detection rate, and assert regeneration is invoked when flagged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.2}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module persistence and state propagation (chat orchestration -> persistence layer -> DB) and can be validated with a real local DB round-trip. Rejected System because behavior text does not require real external HTTP/API contract checks, subprocesses, or OS-level infrastructure beyond local DB interaction.","test_description":"Run end-to-end in-process chat handling with regeneration enabled against a real local test DB; read back persisted records and assert all exchanges are present, ordered, linked to one conversation, and timestamp fields are correctly populated/monotonic.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"Behavior is an externally visible side effect ('customer never sees') and must be proven via boundary round-trip observation, not only internal state checks. This matches SYSTEM TRIAD #3 (externally visible effect via readback). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because this assertion is about exposure/replacement semantics, not model output quality, and can use deterministic model doubles while still requiring real external interface verification.","test_description":"Exercise the deployed service through its real customer-facing interface (e.g., HTTP/chat endpoint), force a regeneration path, and assert client-visible response payload/stream contains only the regenerated response and never includes the rejected draft.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.65,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
